Programming Language used: JAVA

How the code is structured?
AiPlayer.java- MINIMAX algorithm, to fetch optimal solution by returning optimal column from the function when computer plays.
node.java- To create a successor for the parent.
GameBoard.java- This class contains game-board state, function to get next player, keep tracks of empty cells to fill in,prints the gameboard state to a file or in console,
and function to get the score of the player.
Maxconenct4.java- This contains main class. Check if 4 arguments are passed. Based on interactive or one-move the control is passed to computer or human from this function.

How to execute the code?
Check if .class files are present in the src file, if present delete it and compile the code 
Compile the code using- javac Maxconnect4.java GameBoard.java node.java AiPlayer.java

One-Move mode:
java Maxconnect4 one-move Input1.txt output1.txt 1
make sure Input1.txt and output1.txt exists in src folder
after each execution make sure you copy the contains of output1.txt to input1.txt for continuing the game with one-move mode.

Interactive mode:
java Maxconnect4 interactive Input1.txt computer-next 2
for computer-next: it gives human first chance to make a move

for human-next:
java Maxconnect4 interactive Input1.txt human-next 2
for human-next: computer plays first and then human

